Some investigators believe recent increases in malaria incidence in the highlands of East Africa were associated with a warming trend that began in the 1970s (
 Pascual et al. 2006; 
 Patz 2002); others have linked the increases to other factors, including drug resistance (
 Hay et al. 2002a, 
 2002b; 
 Shanks et al. 2002). However, the reality may involve the interaction of multiple factors.
